  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>The Hotel San Giovanni is offered on bed and breakfast.</p>
<p>A continental breakfast is served each morning.</p>
<p>You can book and pay locally to dine in the hotel's restaurant for dinner and enjoy some local dishes and home cooking. You can expect freshly made soups, pastas, rich meat dishes and the homemade pizzas that the hotel is known for. You'll get a 15% discount on food prices. </p>]]></cateringDescription>
  <deactivateThisPage>0</deactivateThisPage>
  <description><![CDATA[<p>You'll be welcomed into Hotel San Giovanni with open arms. This small and friendly family-run hotel has an ideal location 20 metres away from the ski lift. It'll connect you to the Carosello gondola and you can ski almost all the way back to the hotel. The centre of <a data-udi="umb://document/e469a37cba1c498e9197c6963def7b89" href="/%7blocalLink:umb:/document/e469a37cba1c498e9197c6963def7b89%7d" title="Livigno">Livigno</a> is around two kilometres, however you can just hop on the free resort bus which takes you to the centre and the lifts for the Mottolino side of the mountain.</p>
<h2>Cosy hotel</h2>
<p>With its traditional alpine furnishings, the hotel radiates a cosy and friendly atmosphere. You'll receive a warm welcome from the team, be sure to ask them for their recommendations on the best place to ski or stop for a bite to eat.  When you return from a day on the slopes, the hotel and lounge is a great spot to catch up with friends and family with a drink or two. The bar's open to the public so there is a good après atmosphere. If you're a little peckish, treat yourself to a snack from the hotel's pizzeria. </p>
<h2>Bed and breakfast</h2>
<p>The San Giovanni is offered on a bed and breakfast basis, so you can head into Livigno centre and enjoy dining in some of the tasty local restaurants. The hotel has its own restaurant which we recommend heading to during your stay - serving tasty classic Italian dishes and typical regional dishes from the Valtellina, and pizzas cooked in a wood-fired oven, it's an excellent choice. The wine cellar has a great selection of regional wines from <a data-udi="umb://document/996aa9008def4ffe9a331c775cc97902" href="/{localLink:umb://document/996aa9008def4ffe9a331c775cc97902}" title="Italy">Italy</a>, so there's bound to be a wine which pairs nicely with your meal.</p>
<h3>Exclusive to Inghams</h3>
<p>As a ski specialist tour operator we carefully select the very best accommodation in our resorts and package them with flights and transfers, so that you can make the most of your holiday. We have an exclusive agreement with Hotel San Giovanni the only UK tour operator to package and sell holidays here - all the more reason to book with Inghams today!</p>]]></description>
